{"blocks":[{"key":"1gefo","text":"Instructor Tips","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":15}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2bq5o","text":"In a more advanced course, I would let students select which enzyme to use (chosen from the ones in the freezer.) In an intro course, I choose the enzyme for them. PvuII is a good choice because it has two cut sites in the backbone and one in the GFP insert. This makes it easy to distinguish between the correct plasmid and one with a GFP still present (maybe not glowing because of a mutation? Or some other error?)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":232,"length":26}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c1fiu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6uv87","text":"PvuII is a little on the expensive side -- but if you're giving the digest a full hour, diluting down to 2 units per ul gives two advantages: it decreases the amount used, and increases the volume of the pipetting step. Make sure you use the correct diluent, though.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"k569","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7thkg","text":"I used to include a heat-inactivation step. I don't any more because the SDS in the purple loading dye denatures the enzyme.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8c083","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3sfrk","text":"Sometimes a student's miniprep isn't concentrated enough to get a full microgram of DNA into the digest. As long as they can get at least 500 ng in the digest, that should be enough to see on a gel. It's more acceptable to decrease the mass of DNA than it is to increase the volume -- contaminants in the miniprep often get in the way of the digest, particularly leftover ethanol.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"132ug","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"duem7","text":"I don't have a positive control in this experiment as written. Maybe add one?","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
